{
  "texts": [
    "After that, we revisit vanilla LoRA and two-subspaces-mixing strategy in a more finegrained view (i.e., rank=1), thus unifying both methods as employing an extra fixed mixer.",
    "Therefore, we propose MoSLoRA, which employs a learnable mixer to fuse more information and more flexibly.",
    "The mixer requires negligible extra parameters and computing costs.",
    "Experimental results on commonsense reasoning tasks, visual instruction tuning tasks, and subject-driven generation tasks demonstrate the effectiveness and robustness of the proposed MoSLoRA.",
    "For future work, we would consider applying MoSLoRA for more tasks."
  ]
}